"Lately, I’ve been really busy with work, so I don’t usually take the initiative to ask friends out for a meal. But once in a while, a friend will invite me out. Since it doesn’t happen often, I really value the chance to catch up and have a good chat."

"Lately, work has been keeping me so busy that I rarely have the time or energy to reach out and make plans with friends. Still, every now and then, a friend will invite me out for a meal. Since those moments are few and far between, I truly cherish them — it’s a wonderful chance to reconnect, share stories, and enjoy some much-needed time together."



得手不得手

私は英語のリスニングが不得手で、いつもテストに苦労します。
機械の操作は不得手なので、よく人に頼んでいます。
不得手なことでも、努力すれば少しずつ上達します。
彼は整理整頓が不得手で、いつも机の上が散らかっています。
運動が不得手なので、体育の授業はあまり好きではありません。


